    <introduction>
        <p>
        Before we begin the study of partial differential equations (PDEs), we need to make sure we have a strong command of ordinary differential equations (ODEs) and multivariable Calculus. These topics must be understood <term>both</term> from a procedural point of view and conceptually. In this worksheet you'll test your understanding and procedural proficiency with ODEs, on Wednesday we'll do multivariable Calculus. The goal right now is to find out where we stand with background material.
        </p>
    </introduction>
<page>
