<exercise><title>Solving Exercises</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            For each of these questions, and all that you answer from now on, you need to <em>explain</em> your reasoning as you go. At the end of the question, if possible, try to conclude with a statement saying why the answer you obtained makes sense from a practical point of view. 
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A brine solution containing <m>0.25</m> kg of salt per liter of water flows into a <m>100</m>L mixing vat at a rate of <m>5</m> L/min. A well-stirred mixture leaves at a rate of <m>6</m> L/min. If the vat is initially full of fresh water, find a formula for the quantity <m>Q</m> of salt in the tank as a function of time.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A damped oscillator is governed by the 2nd order ODE
<md>
y''+6y'+13y = 0
</md>
when no external force is applied to it. Its initial position is <m>y(0)=0</m> and has a velocity of <m>y'(0) =2</m>. At <m>t=3</m>, an external force of <m>F(t) = 2\cos(3t)</m> is applied. Show that, in the long run, <m>y(t)</m> is approximately a periodic function. What is the period and amplitude of this function?
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>

    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Consider the second order ODE
<md>
(1-t^2)y''-2ty'+n(n+1)y = 0.
</md>
Suppose <m>n</m> is a non-negative integer. By guessing a power series solution, show that this equation has a polynomial solution for some initial conditions. Does it have polynomial solutions for <em>all</em> initial conditions?
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>

</exercise>



